1 olive oil
1 beetroot
1 carrot
1 parsnip
1 potato
1 packet Pumpkin Seeds (Pepitas)
½ lemon
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet chicken breast
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet roasted almonds
1 bag parsley
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut
the beetroot into small chunks. Cut the carrot,
parsnip and potato into bite-sized chunks. Place
the veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive
oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat,
spread out evenly, then roast until tender,
25-30 minutes. When the veggies have 5 minutes
cook time remaining, remove the tray from the
oven, sprinkle over the pumpkin seeds and roast
until toasted. Allow to cool slightly.

While the veggies are roasting, zest the lemon to
get a pinch, then slice into wedges. Finely chop the
parsley. In a small bowl, combine the garlic aioli,
lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice, a drizzle of
olive oil and 1/2 the parsley, then season.
Set aside.

Place your hand flat on top of each chicken breast
and slice through horizontally to make two thin
steaks. In a medium bowl, combine the Aussie
spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil, then season.
Add the chicken and turn to coat. Set aside.

When the veggies have 10 minutes cook time
remaining, heat a large frying pan over a
medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook
the chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes
each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting
crowded). Remove from the heat and set aside.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this
adds to the flavour!

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer
pink inside!

Add the spinach & rocket mix to the roasted
veggies and pumpkin seeds and gently toss to
combine.

Slice the golden chicken. Roughly chop the
roasted almonds. Divide the roast root veggie
salad between plates. Top with the chicken.
Drizzle over the herby garlic aioli. Garnish with the
almonds and remaining parsley. Serve with any
remaining lemon wedges.